TreesPlease Games Privacy and Cookies Policy
Last updated: 9th February 2023
Summary
We are Treesplease Games Ltd, a company incorporated under the laws of England and Wales with company number 12223638 and registered office at Preston Park House, South Road, Brighton, East Sussex, United Kingdom, BN1 6SB ( ‘
TreesPlease
’, ‘
we
’ or ‘
us
’).
This policy describes the ways in which we collect and use personal data about you when you use our website at
https://www.treespleasegames.com
, when you play our games and you otherwise interact with us, for example, when you contact us with a query or when you engage with us in the course of your employment with one of our service providers or business partners.
Personal data
is information from which you can be directly or indirectly identified (for example, name and email address, username and password).
We may change this policy from time to time so please check our website regularly to keep up-to-date with any updates.
This policy was last changed in May 2022.
For the purposes of data protection legislation, we are the controller of personal data we process about you. This means that we are responsible for the security of the personal data and the decisions we make regarding the personal data.
We have registered with the Information Commissioner’s Office (“
ICO
”) as a controller and our registration number is ZB265376.
1. What personal data do we collect about you?
Playing the game
When you log in to play our game we collect basic account log in information such as your username or information related to your account with Facebook, Apple or Google (such as names and email addresses) received by us when you  log-in to our game via Facebook, Apple or Google.
We may attach a unique reference ID to you as a player.
Advertising and marketing strategy
We and third party advertising service providers may collect the following information about you and your device, some of which amounts to personal data about you:
gameplay information:
your use of the game, for example, your actions within the game, your progress within the game, your preferences, your in-app purchases and your session time and metrics
third party platform information:
your use of third party social media and other online platforms
device identifiers:
IDFA (identifier for advertisers), Android ID (in Android devices); Google Advertiser ID, any user IDs issued by us about you and other similar unique identifiers
device information:
this refers to technical information about your mobile device such as: device type and model, CPU, system language, memory, OS version, Wi-Fi status and time stamp zone.
We may also collect personal data used to promote our offerings on third party websites and platforms, for example, information regarding demographics, interests and behaviours.
Social media
We may receive personal data about you such as opinions and comments you make via social media, when you interact with our accounts on social media and other online platforms, for example, when you post something on our LinkedIn page or when you tag us on one of your Facebook posts.
Website and correspondence
We may also collect personal data about your use of the website, your preferences on the website and information about your device when you use our website (please see the section titled
Cookies
below). We may also receive any data that is included in any correspondence you have with our team or when an individual mentions you in any correspondence they send to us.
2. How do we collect your personal data?
Playing our game
We mostly collect personal data directly from you. We may also receive your personal data via Apple, Google or Facebook when you log-in to our game via Apple, Google or Facebook.
Advertising and marketing strategy
We may also receive information relating to your engagement with our game and your preferences or activities on third party platforms or websites, which might be used as part of our performance marketing strategy from third party marketing partners, such as Facebook.
We engage a number of advertising partners that collect and provide us with a number of device and advertising identifiers and information in the form of aggregated data reports to help us understand how our marketing strategy is performing and to promote our game to you and potential new players. These partners also help us provide tailored marketing to you whilst you are playing the game.
Social media
We may also collect your personal data through social media platforms such as LinkedIn and Facebook when you use tools to tag us and mention us in your posts, statuses and comments through your accounts on these platforms, and when you provide us with your personal data on our accounts on these platforms, e.g. when you comment on one of our posts on Facebook.
Correspondence
We may also collect your personal data when you email us or otherwise contact us. We may also receive your personal data through other individuals who may, for example, mention you in any communications they send to us.
Other third parties
We may collect your personal data from any other types of organisations listed in the section titled
Sharing your information with third parties
below.
3. How do we use your personal data?
In accordance with data protection laws, we will only process your personal data if we have a lawful basis for doing so.
In respect of your personal data, these bases are:
if it is necessary to provide services to you under the performance of a contract we have with you
if we are required to do so in accordance with legal obligations
if you have given your consent
if it is in our legitimate interests to process your personal data, provided that none of these prejudice your own rights, freedoms and interests.
The following is a list of the purposes for which we process your personal data, and the lawful bases on which we carry out such processing.
