5. Links to third party websites and third party adverts
TreesPlease is not responsible for the privacy policies and practices of other sites even if you access them via our website and/or as part of playing the game. You should check the policy of each site you visit and contact its owner or operator if you have any concerns or questions.
6. International Transfers
Some of the parties we share your personal data with might be based abroad. When we transfer personal data outside the UK and EEA we are required to ensure you are afforded equivalent protection in respect of your personal data to that provided in the UK and the EU.
Generally, we will put in place appropriate safeguards when making international transfers, for example, by using specific contractual clauses which have been approved by the
European Commission
and/or the
UK government
together with supplementary measures if we deem it necessary in the circumstances, for example, further contractual commitments, enhanced security and assessments of transfer risk.
7. Retention
We retain your data for no longer than is reasonable in line with the purposes for which it was originally collected, including for the purposes of satisfying any contractual requirements or other legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.
To determine the appropriate retention period for personal data, we consider the purposes for which we process the personal data, the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal data, the potential risk of harm from unauthorised use or disclosure of your personal data, whether we can achieve those purposes through other means and the applicable legal requirements.
7. Cookies
What are Cookies?
For simplicity, in this policy we use the term Cookies to refer to cookies and other tracking technologies. Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device or browser and read information on your device or browser when you use the website and/or play the game.
Cookies set by us are called ‘first party cookies’. Cookies set by third parties (i.e. domains we do not operate) are called ‘third party cookies’.
Session cookies
enable you to move from page to page within our website and/or play our  game and any information you enter will be remembered but is deleted when you close the page or session or after a short time.
Persistent cookies
allow us to remember your preferences and settings when you use our website and/or play the game in the future.
We will obtain your consent for the implementation of any Cookies that are not Necessary Cookies (as described below).
Disabling Cookies:
Website:
The use of the Cookies improves the functionality of our website and our game. If you do not want these Cookies to be served on your device, you are able to disable them by changing the settings on the website or on your device. These settings are usually found in the 'options' or 'preferences' menu of your internet browser. You may be able to block cookies from by activating the setting on your browser that allows you to refuse the setting of cookies. Please note that if you do decide to disable cookies you may not be able to access some of the website, and some of the features of the website may not function properly.
Types of Cookies we use:
We currently use the following types of Cookies on our website and game:
Necessary
Those that are necessary for the operation of the website and the game, including allowing you to interact with our website and the game and to recall selections as you move between pages and different parts of the game and which enable core functionality such as security, credentials authentication, network management and accessibility and to determine changes in information you provide to the website and the game.
Website: We only use a crumb cookie on the website which is used to prevent attacks.
Performance (analytics)
Those that analyse the use of and game, for example, to help analyse how players use our game. We use this information to identify trends and improve our game.
Functional
Those that are used to provide certain functionalities within our game and to remember choices you make so we can personalise the content of the game for you.
Advertising (targeting)
Those that are used to deliver advertisements about our game within third party websites and apps [and advertisements about other products and services within our game].
We use Cookies from different advertising service providers, which allow us to track how our advertising campaigns are doing and deliver advertising to you.
More information:
To find out more about
how cookies work, how to manage and delete them and to see which ones have been set please visit
www.aboutcookies.org
or
www.allaboutcookies.org
.
8. Your rights
Exercising your rights:
You can contact us using the details set out below if you wish to exercise your data protection rights. We may require you to provide forms of identity should you wish to exercise one of your rights below.
Access
: You are entitled to confirmation that we process your personal data and a copy of such personal data.
Rectification
: If the personal data we hold about you is incorrect, you have the right for this to be rectified. You may also update your personal data through your account settings.
Erasure
: You can request us to erase your personal data if there is no compelling reason to continue processing.
Restriction
: You may request a restriction on the processing we undertake on your personal data.  This will only apply if we have no lawful basis to process your personal data, your personal data is inaccurate or to comply with an objection request (see below).
Objection
: You may object to our processing of your personal data if our processing is carried out on the basis of legitimate interests. Please note, however, that should we determine that our interests are so compelling as to override your objection we may continue to process your personal data.
You may object to receiving direct marketing at any time.
Portability
: You have the right to receive some of your personal data in machine readable format.  This right extends to you being able to request that such data is sent to a third-party controller.
Withdrawing consent
: If the lawful basis we rely on to process your personal data is consent you have the right to withdraw this consent. Please email
privacy@treespleasegames.com
to withdraw consent for the processing of your personal data.
Complaining to a supervisory authority
: Further information about your rights can also be obtained from your national data protection regulator – in the UK, this is the Information Commissioner’s Office (
https://ico.org.uk/
). If you have any cause for complaint about our use of your personal data, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your national data protection supervisory authority, although we would ask that you contact us in the first instance.
Your right to be informed
: You can contact us to find out more or to ask any questions you may have about our use of your personal data.
